# 🏀 NBA Game Outcome Prediction
### Data Mining Techniques for Accurate Basketball Forecasting
![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-3.10-blue)
![Accuracy](https://img.shields.io/badge/Best%20Accuracy-98%25-brightgreen)
![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)
## 📌 Overview
This project applies multiple machine learning classification algorithms to predict
the outcomes of NBA basketball games (Win/Loss) using game-level statistics from
the 2019–2024 seasons. The best model, a Hybrid Ensembled Classifier, achieves 98%.
Submitted as MSc Data Analytics thesis, Dublin Business School, January 2025.
## 📊 Dataset
- Source: basketball-reference.com + NBA official site
- Seasons: 2019–2024 (5 seasons, 30 teams, 82 games/team)
- Records: ~12,300 games | Shape after cleaning: 14,118 × 28
- Target: W/L (binary classification: Win=1, Loss=0)
Key features include: True Shooting %, Effective FG%, Defensive Rating,
Offensive Rating, Turnover %, Steal %, Block %, Rebound %, and more.
