## ⚙️ Installation
```bash
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/nba-game-prediction.git
cd nba-game-prediction
pip install -r requirements.txt
```
Or open the .ipynb directly in Google Colab — no local setup needed.
## 📦 Requirements
pandas>=1.5  numpy>=1.23  scikit-learn>=1.2  lightgbm>=3.3
catboost>=1.2  mlxtend>=0.22  imbalanced-learn>=0.10  plotly>=5.0
## 🤖 Models & Results
| Model                      | Accuracy |
|----------------------------|----------|
| Logistic Regression        |   89%    |
| Decision Tree Classifier   |   86%    |
| Random Forest Classifier   |   93%    |
| AdaBoost Classifier        |   93%    |
| CatBoost Classifier        |   95%    |
| LightGBM Classifier        |   93%    |
| **Hybrid Ensembled** ⭐     | **98%**  |
## 🔬 Methodology
1. Business Understanding (CRISP-DM)
2. Data Collection & Loading (CSV from basketball-reference.com)
3. Data Cleaning (drop dupes, rename columns, datetime conversion)
4. EDA (14+ interactive Plotly visualisations)
5. Preprocessing (LabelEncoder, stratified split, SMOTE)
6. Feature Selection (ExtraTreesClassifier importance)
7. Model Training & Evaluation (7 classifiers)
8. Hybrid Ensemble Stacking (best model — 98%)
## 🏆 Hybrid Ensembled Classifier Architecture
Base Classifiers (Layer 1):
  ├── LGBMClassifier     (n_estimators=8,  max_depth=6)
  ├── CatBoostClassifier (n_estimators=6,  max_depth=6)
  └── RandomForest       (n_estimators=6)
Meta Classifier (Layer 2): AdaBoostClassifier (n_estimators=5)
## 📁 Key Features
- Full CRISP-DM methodology applied
- 14+ interactive EDA visualisations (Plotly)
- 7 ML models benchmarked with confusion matrices
- Novel stacked ensemble architecture (98% accuracy)
- MSc thesis-level documentation and academic references
